Talk by P Sainath [4 Nov 6pm]; Music Concert by Vishwa Mohan Bhatt [5 Nov 5.45pm]; 

Dear members,

We are having two events this week, and a drinks reception hosted by O.P.
Jindal University:
1. Tue 4 Nov: Talk by P Sainath
2. Tue 4 Nov: O.P. Jindal Global University drinks reception
3. Wed 5 Nov: OIS & SPIC MACAY Music Concert by Vishwa Mohan Bhatt

===============================================================================
P Sainath will be talking on:
 Journalism from Below: People's Archive of Rural India
 and the Everyday Lives of Everyday People

P Sainath is an acclaimed reporter, Magsaysay Award winner and the author
of 'Everybody Loves a Good Drought'.

Location: Flora Anderson Hall, Somerville College
 *** NOTE *** Venue has changed ****
Time: 4 Nov 2014 6pm

Organised with the Oxford India Centre for Sustainable Development.

===============================================================================
O.P. Jindal Global University Drinks Reception, followed by Dinner

OP Jindal Global University (JGU) is hosting a drinks reception
and interaction, followed by a dinner at Somerville College on Tuesday,
November 4th, 2014, starting at 6pm. The event will be attended by the
founding Vice Chancellor Professor (Dr.) C Raj Kumar and the Principal
Director Professor (Dr.) Sanjeev P Sahni. JGU currently has
five interdisciplinary schools and offers programmes in law, business,
international affairs, public policy and liberal arts & humanities.

The event aims at discussing the various opportunities available at
JGU with students who would be interested in taking up faculty
positions. 

See http://posters.oxfordindiasociety.org.uk/invitation-somerville-college-4-nov-2014.pdf
for more details about the event.

===============================================================================
OIS & SPIC MACAY: Music Concert by Vishwa Mohan Bhatt

It gives us great pleasure to present a music concert by the acclaimed
Vishwa Mohan Bhatt, winner of a Grammy Award and creator of the Mohan Veena
at the Holywell Music Room.

Book early for an enchanting evening. You can buy tickets at
http://www.eventbrite.com/e/ois-spic-macay-music-concert-by-vishwa-mohan-bhatt-tickets-13795728395?aff=eac2

Tickets: £6 students, £9 non-students
Location: Holywell Music Room, Holywell Street, Oxford
Time: 5 Nov 2014 5.45-8pm

See the poster at
http://posters.oxfordindiasociety.org.uk/20141105_concert_vm_bhatt

